footnotes.desc: Descriptive terms (soft, firm, extra firm) vary in usage between manufacturers as there are no standards for the various types of tofu.
Manufacturers use either magnesium chloride (nigari), calcium sulfate, or both in varying quantities to precipitate the protein.  Calcium and magnesium contents will vary accordingly.
